The '''1994 Pennsylvania United States Senate election''' was held on November 8, 1994 to select the [[United States Senate|U.S. Senator]] from the state of [[Pennsylvania]].  [[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]] Senator [[Harris Wofford]] decided to seek re-election, but was defeated by Republican [[Rick Santorum]], who represented [[Pennsylvania's 18th congressional district]]. <ref>http://www.ourcampaigns.com/RaceDetail.html?RaceID=3458</ref>

